HEADWORD: Sida
<hw>Si"da</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/<?/<?/ a kind of plant.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of
malvaceous plants common in the tropics. All the species are
mucilaginous, and some have tough ligneous fibers which are used as a
substitute for hemp and flax.</def> <rj><au>Balfour (Cyc. of
India).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

